# Rondo Mundi Backend

This is the backend for the Rondo Mundi lottery application, implemented in Rust using [Actix Web](https://actix.rs/).

## Features

- Create and manage lotteries
- Buy tickets for active lotteries
- Pick a winner using cryptographically secure randomness
- View details of individual lotteries
- List all lotteries
- Health check endpoint

## API Endpoints

- `GET /health` — Health check
- `POST /lottery` — Create a new lottery
- `GET /lottery/{lottery_id}` — Get details of a lottery
- `POST /lottery/{lottery_id}/buy` — Buy tickets for a lottery
- `POST /lottery/{lottery_id}/pick_winner` — Pick a winner (admin only)
- `GET /lotteries` — List all lotteries

## Running Locally

1. **Install Rust**: https://rustup.rs/
2. **Install dependencies**:  
   In the `backend` directory, run:
   ```sh
   cargo build
   ```
3. **Run the server**:  
   ```sh
   cargo run
   ```
   The server will start on `0.0.0.0:8080`.

